3ï¸âƒ£ How to reference templates in views
# boats/views.py
from django.shortcuts import render

def boat_list(request):
    return render(request, 'boats/list.html')

# accounts/views.py
def login_view(request):
    return render(request, 'accounts/login.html')

4ï¸âƒ£ Base Template (Professional)

templates/base.html â€“ shared layout for all apps:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>{% block title %}SeaSmart{% endblock %}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">
</head>
<body>
    {% include 'navbar.html' %}
    
    <div class="container">
        {% block content %}
        {% endblock %}
    </div>

    {% include 'footer.html' %}
    <script src="{% static 'js/main.js' %}"></script>
</body>
</html>

âœ… App template extending base
<!-- boats/templates/boats/list.html -->
{% extends 'base.html' %}

{% block title %}Boats List{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<h1>All Boats</h1>
<ul>
    <!-- loop boats -->
</ul>
{% endblock %}

5ï¸âƒ£ Naming Conventions (Professional)
Aspect	Recommendation
App templates folder	<app_name> inside templates/
Template files	lowercase, underscore, descriptive (list.html, detail.html)
Shared templates	project-level templates/ (base.html, navbar.html)
Static files	grouped by type (css/, js/, images/)
App-level static (optional)	apps/<app>/static/<app>/css/...
6ï¸âƒ£ Django Settings (settings.py)
TEMPLATES = [
    {
        'BACKEND': 'django.template.backends.django.DjangoTemplates',
        'DIRS': [BASE_DIR / 'templates'],  # project-level templates
        'APP_DIRS': True,  # app-level templates auto-detect
        'OPTIONS': {
            'context_processors': [
                'django.template.context_processors.debug',
                'django.template.context_processors.request',
                'django.contrib.auth.context_processors.auth',
                'django.contrib.messages.context_processors.messages',
            ],
        },
    },
]


